#text=I decided to bake a cake for my daughter 's birthday .
#text=I had gone to the grocery store to buy one , but nothing looked very good and they were really expensive for what I was getting .
#text=I figured that I could make a better cake myself .
#text=I figured that I have seen cooking shows and said , '' `` How hard could it be ? '' ''
#text=I bought a Betty Crocker Triple Chocolate Fudge cake mix and I thought it looked pretty good .
#text=I went to the frosting and found some Oreo frosting mix and thought it would be perfect because my daughter loves Oreo cookies .
#text=Then , I grabbed a box of Oreo cookies , some eggs , milk , and some oil .
#text=I did not know if I had all of that at home , but I figured they would not go to waste .
#text=I came home and mixed everything and put it in the oven .
#text=I tested the cake before taking it out of the oven with a toothpick .
#text=Coming out clean , I decided the cake was done .
#text=I had pour the cake mix into two baking pans because my plan was to make a two layered cake .
#text=I saw on a cooking show that you are supposed to cut the top of one of the cakes so that the top was flat .
#text=I managed to do that pretty well and I ate the cake with some milk .
#text=So , next , I got the frosting and put it on the first layer , and then on the second .
#text=I carefully chopped some oreos up and sprinkled them on the top of the cake .
#text=To further top it off , I cut a few cookies in half and stuck them pointing up in a circle around the outside of the cake .
#text=My wife was really surprised that I had made it myself .
#text=My daughter was really happy and everyone liked the cake .
